FLAS
HERBARIUM

University of Florida Herbarium
Florida Museum of Natural History

FLAS 275423

PLANTS OF NORTH CAROLINA
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt
det. Michelle Gaynor, 31 May 2021

STOKES COUNTY: Hanging Rock State Park, Hanging rock trail, very close to specimen 52. Elev. 515 – 516 m. Under oak (spp. unknown) and *Kalmia latifolia*. Co-occurring species include maple saplings and true moss (unknown spp.). Flowering, with top of spike still in bed. Leaves mix of new and old.

Lat. 36.391982  Long. -80.26509404 Datum: WGS84
coll. Michelle Gaynor # 53 31 May 2021

North Carolina Division of Parks and Recreation, Scientific Research and Collecting Permit, 2021_0524. Corresponds to genetic sample MLG245 (Pop 17).

Ploidy level inferred via flow cytometry: Tetraploid.
Michelle L. Gaynor 7 Sept 2022

*Kalmia latifolia*
